[Overview]

<p>Variable, surprising, overall usable even on OU teams.</p>

[SET]
name: Baton Pass
move 1: AncientPower
move 2: Baton Pass
move 3: Softboiled / Wish
move 4: Fire Blast / Flamethrower
item: Leftovers
ability: Serene Grace
nature: Calm / Sassy
evs: 252 HP / 120 Def / 136 SpD

[SET COMMENTS]

<p>Keep using AncientPower, hope to get the boost (20% chance with Serene Grace), beat the crap out of the Skarmory that comes to Roar / Whirlwind you. Pity Togetic doesn't get Thunderbolt or Thunder to deal with both Skarmory and Suicune. Togetic needs Fire Blast to 2HKO Skarmory, but if you absolutely hate missing, Flamethrower is still an option. You have a 33.6% chance to get one AncientPower boost, 29.4% chance to get 2 boosts, a 14.7% chance to get 3 boosts, and a 5.52% chance to get 4 or more boosts, assuming you hit with all 8 PP.</p>

[SET]
name: 2v2 Standard
move 1: Follow Me
move 2: Counter
move 3: Softboiled / Light Screen / Reflect
move 4: Thunder Wave / Seismic Toss
item: Leftovers
ability: Serene Grace
nature: Calm
evs: 252 HP / 160 Def / 96 SpD

[SET COMMENTS]

<p>This is a 2v2 set. Use this with a Pokemon with a way to set up and a good attack stat. People might use Rock Slide to hit both Pokemon, so Counter them back. Thunder Wave is a good support move, and Softboiled is for healing, though Togetic can't survive many attacks in 2v2.</p>

[Other Options]

<p>Charm helps against physical attackers, and Yawn can force switches.</p>

<p>Togetic learns many support moves, figure something out yourself. The above sets are just random ideas that came to mindâ€”you can pass Wishes, Mirror Move Spikes, etc.</p>

[EVs]

<p>Togetic has excellent Special Defense and nice Defense, so boost HP and one of those stats.</p>

[Checks and Counters]

<p>Any STAB Rock-type attack can KO Togetic. It is also weak offensively. You can easily Substitute against it and boost your stats or just pound it with attacks. But watch out for Thunder Wave.</p>